---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Link from '../components/Link.astro';
import TableOfContents from '../components/TableOfContents.astro';
const title = 'LUT - Cities Skylines Modding';
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets';
import { images } from '../data/imageImports.js';
---

<MainLayout title={title}>
	<TableOfContents />
	<section class="pt-12 pb-48 sm:ml-64 xl:mr-64 text-lg text-hit-gray-500">
		<h1 id="overview" class="border-b-4 border-hit-gray-600 pb-8 text-4xl font-bold text-hit-gray-400">LUT</h1>
		<div class="content">
			<h2 class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400" id="about">
				<a
					href="#about"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>About
				</a>
			</h2>

			<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-6 mt-4">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>
						LUT stands for look-up table. It's a map of colors which allows applying color correction and
						adjustments to the image.
					</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/lut/comp.jpg" target="_blank">
						<Picture
							src={images.comp}
							width={images.comp.width / 2}
							densities={[1.5, 2]}
							formats={['avif', 'webp']}
							alt="Comparison between the default LUT without any adjustments and a finished modified LUT"
							class="h-auto w-full aspect-video object-cover"
							loading="eager"
						/></a
					><p class="explanation">
						Comparison between the default LUT without any adjustments and a finished modified LUT. Using <a
							href="https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=1209581656">Relight</a
						> with default/recommended settings.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h4
				class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12"
				id="folder"
			>
				<a
					href="#folder"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Folder</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">The folder where you should put the LUT png is located here:</p>
			<p class="mt-4">
				<span class="path">%LocalAppData%\Colossal Order\Cities_Skylines\Addons\ColorCorrections</span>
			</p>
			<p class="mt-4">
				The AppData folder is hidden by default, you can access it by copying and pasting the path into the file
				explorer, or pressing
				<span class="key">Windows + R</span> and typing in appdata.
			</p>
			<h2 class="border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 mt-24 pb-8 text-4xl font-medium text-hit-gray-400" id="creation">
				Creation
			</h2>
		</div>
		<h3 class="pb-4 mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-500" id="default-lut">
			<a
				href="#default-lut"
				title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
				>Default LUT</a
			>
		</h3>
		<p class="mt-4">To create an LUT, you first need to download the default LUT which has no adjustments.</p>
		<div class="content-download mt-4">
			<Link classes="" href="https://i.imgur.com/cgjH2nC.png" text="Download" theme="downloadbutton" />
		</div>
		<h3 class="pb-4 mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-500" id="adjustments">
			<a
				href="#adjustments"
				title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
				>Adjustments</a
			>
		</h3>
		<p class="mt-4">
			You should only apply per-pixel color adjustments, that means you cannot apply effects such as blur,
			sharpening, clarity, highlights/shadows, and many other effects which are more than just a simple color
			adjustment.
		</p>
		<p class="mt-4">
			You can apply color adjustments such as brightness, contrast, levels, curves, exposure, vibrance,
			saturation, hue, color balance, black &amp; white, color lookups, gradient maps, and selective color.
		</p>
		<h3
			class="pb-4 mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-500"
			id="16 bits/channel"
		>
			<a
				href="#16 bits/channel"
				title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
				>16 bits/channel</a
			>
		</h3>
		<p class="mt-4">
			When many adjustments are applied, working with a 16 bits/channel image can have the benefits of less noise
			and banding issues. But make sure the final image is exported as 8 bits/channel, otherwise, the game won't
			recognize it.
		</p>
		<h2 class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400" id="example">
			<a
				href="#example"
				title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
				>Example</a
			>
		</h2>
		<p class="mt-4">
			Download a Photoshop file of an example LUT with various adjustments. Must be exported as 8 bits/channel
			png.
		</p>
		<div class="content-download mt-4">
			<Link
				classes=""
				href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=1JuKMQ07VkDs_ZMVoFyvaRhowQ7N-vMrt"
				text="Download"
				theme="downloadbutton"
			/>
		</div>
	</section>
</MainLayout>
